href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid VS Ranger</span><hr size=1> Come on people, give me a hand <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><i>Aludiwen Someshta</i> - Druid of Tunare of the 30th Circle, Drinal, Dark Phoenix Alliance</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugielgiel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Giel Giel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/23/02 5:26:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid VS Ranger</span><hr size=1> buff yourself up fully, put all your crap buffs up first.  If you land Ensare on him then you will win the fight. If not, you can still win but you'll have to stay out of melee range as much as possible while u cast.<br>
<br>
Sacrifice all your gear to get the highest MR you can, cuz if he sticks snare on you, then you're screwed.<br>
<br>
ensnare<br>
drones<br>
immolate<br>
combust..repeat till he is dead<br>
<br>
really  not much brain surgery involved, even with a melee that has good archery skills, cuz you'll channel thru those hits. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualudiwensomeshta.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aludiwen Someshta</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/23/02 9:37:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid VS Ranger</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the advice, I thought that if you were snared and how cast SOW on yourself then SOW would cancel snare... or is this just a rumor? <p><i>Aludiwen Someshta</i> - Druid of Tunare of the 30th Circle, Drinal, Dark Phoenix Alliance</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulaniris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laniris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/24/02 1:22:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid VS Ranger</span><hr size=1> Lemme see here...<br>
First of all you need MR gear, and lots of it.  This isn't easy to come by at your level, but whatever you can pick up (like a shiny brass shield...) will be of GREAT help to you.  Like another poster said, you snared = you dead.  Even if he's snared also, his ranged attack will eventually wear you down since he can do it while he's running and you can't cast except by being still.  Not sure if you can get this high enough for it to matter though<br>
<br>
Snare overwrites SoW and SoW recast won't re-overwrite.  Some people like to have sow first on the list so that it can be debuffed easily, but I dunno how much time you'll have to debuff and then recast.<br>
<br>
My suggestion is go figure out what spells he has/doesn't have.  For instance, rangers don't get see invis until level 39, and so casting camoflage on yourself will a) make him unable to see you and b) un-target you (thank you PvP patch in the fall!)  Keep your damage shield up--his weapons are all quick 1h weapons, it's a lot like fighting a monk.  Start him off with your swarm line dot... it's almost impossible to resist and does good damage, even as you stay out of his way. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulaurenia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laurenia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/24/02 8:29:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid VS Ranger</span><hr size=1> personally, im sure you CAN cast spells while moving. but only if you are coming to a stop. dont worry about archery, because you will have regen by then, and it will help negate all the arrow hits. also, you can try rooting him. its not a really sure thing, but you can try if things are going wrong.<br>
like, if he snares you, root, med, mem you cancel magic spell, dispell til you hit snare. put sow in your 4th buff slot, and keep trying to dispell till you get rid of it. remember, if you are caught while snared, its hard to escape the rangers melee skills. also, post what your specialization is. then we can probably come up with the most mana-efficient strategy for ya <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><IMG SRC = "http://laurenia.homestead.com/files/laurenia_sig_final.jpg" WIDTH=383 HEIGHT=223  BORDER=0></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualudiwensomeshta.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aludiwen Someshta</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/24/02 9:15:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid VS Ranger</span><hr size=1> My specialization is alteration (I'm level 30 so it is not very high yet, only around 58 or 60, because I just got it).  I thank you guys for all your help, you are very knowledgable =).  As for Laurenia's comment about snaring/SOW dispelling, I'm a little confused.  Here are a few questions:<br>
<br>
1. What slot should I put SOW on me and why?<br>
<br>
2. Let's say I am SOWed and I get snared, what is the quickest way to get rid of it?  Can I just cancel magic, or do I have to sow myself, then cancel and re-sow?<br>
<br>
3. How does wolf form factor into all of this?  It is better to use wolf form in duels because it lasts longer?  Or does it have some weird dispelling issues with snare?<br>
<br>
Thanks =) <p><i>Aludiwen Someshta</i> - Druid of Tunare of the 30th Circle, Drinal, Dark Phoenix Alliance</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaerostale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerostale</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/24/02 6:53:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid VS Ranger</span><hr size=1> Snare will overwrite sow and wolf form, put SoW/Wolf Form in the first slot so if you get snared it can be dispelled right away. At 34/35 you can probably damage shield yourself and still get combust or greater healing off inbetween hits. The ranger will eat himself alive from the damage shield while you can heal yourself. <br>
You would be suprised at how fast someone's health will go down from a damage shield. <p>
