</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugielgiel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Giel Giel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/24/02 7:42:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid VS Ranger</span><hr size=1> snare overrides your sow/wolf buff.  so if you have sow as your 4th buff and get snared then you got 3 buffs that you need to click off, before you try and dispell snare wth cancel magic. once snare is gone you can recast sow on yourself<br>
<br>
don't bother with wolf form, no point really unless you want the xtra attack if u intend to melee.<br>
<br>
snare on top of snare on bottom is the age old question.  if your MR is high enuff then put snare on the bottom cuz chances are you won't get snared. the thought behind sow on bottom of buffs is that those classes that dispel or use pumice even will have to get through all your buffs first before your sow gets canceled.<br>
<br>
if he's  smart ranger he'll dispell you with pumice and also dispell your dots...ya know what i could go on and on about this. do the following and you have  good chance of winning:<br>
<br>
since this is a duel to the death and i'm guessin there will be no zone hopping etc here are the spells to have memmed and buffs to have up:<br>
<br>
Buffs:<br>
1) blank<br>
2) blank<br>
3) Firefist<br>
4) Strength<br>
5) See Invis<br>
6) SoW<br>
7) Bramblecoat<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Resist Cold<br>
9) Resist Fire<br>
10)Skin Like Steel<br>
11)Regen<br>
12)Shield of Brambles<br>
13)Regen<br>
14)Levitate<br>
15)Endure Magic<br>
<br>
spells:<br>
1) Greater Healing<br>
2) SoW<br>
3) Ensnare<br>
3) Drones<br>
4) Immolate<br>
5) Combust<br>
6) Shield of Brambles<br>
7) Cancel Magic<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Invis/Root (not sure how invis works on bluebie server with duels, if he loses targeting cuz of it then great if not then don't use it) if u land ensare then no need for root<br>
<br>
<br>
Ensare, Ensare, Ensnare (hope it sticks after 3 tries..if not you probalby not gonna stick it)<br>
Drones<br>
Immolate<br>
Combust, Combust, so on and so forth<br>
<br>
Don't be afraid to trade blows with him with your DS and regen in the beginning , especially if u get snare to stick...anyway write alot about this but do the above and you should be fine.<br>
